  "elapsed_s": 11.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The following day, my arm swelled terribly from the tattooing, but after a while, the, the, the swelling had subsided.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Some people actually died from this process of tattooing because they, they used the same needle on everybody.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Well, they had a couple of people doing this, and so these couple of tattooing pens, if I may call it that, was used on hundreds and hundreds of women.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the pain was sharp.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's why they held our hands down, but it's much like getting a shot, and, and if, except that you've got quite a few shots.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I've never counted the number of dots, but that's besides the point, really.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This number indicates that I was, I was in, incarcerated in Auschwitz, and that I was-- actually, it was stamped for extermination, that-- but not before they would take full advantage of my strength.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This became so true [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] because I don't think they expected us to live very long on the food that they gave us, which totaled-- it's very easy to actually add up the calories.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I would say approximately between 350 to 450 calories a day.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If I say 500 calories, I am already exaggerating.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And we worked 12 hours a day.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had to get up at, at the crack of dawn each morning and stand in line till 6:00 AM, at which time we would be counted.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And periodically, entire rows of us would be sliced off, sent away, and never to be seen again.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And sometimes this would be from one end of, of the row, or sometimes from the other end, so that we, we never knew where we would be safe.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
